<section class="explainer section">
  <div class="container explainer__grid">
    <div>
      <span class="section__eyebrow">What is a Personal AI?</span>
      <h2 class="section__title">Not Another Chatbot. <span class="highlight">A Second Brain.</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="explainer__body">
      <p>
        Most AI assistants forget you the moment a session ends. A <strong>personal AI</strong> is different:
        it builds a running understanding of who you are — your preferences, your history, your context —
        and carries that forward into every conversation, on every platform you use.
      </p>
      <p>
        PersonalAI.cloud is built specifically for that job. Instead of one closed chat window, it's a
        <strong>gateway</strong> that sits between you and the model of your choice — OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq,
        Mistral, Gemini, DeepSeek, NVIDIA NIM, or a fully local model via Ollama — while a persistent memory
        layer (PostgreSQL + pgvector, retrieved through RAG) keeps the context that any single model would
        otherwise lose.
      </p>
      <p>
        That means the same memory follows you from a WhatsApp message, to the web app, to Android — and it
        stays yours: never used to train a base model, deletable on demand, and fully self-hostable if you'd
        rather run the whole stack on your own hardware.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

